oc:kn_1b21d4d1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When the project has many Spring proxied classes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Consider applying the allopen compiler plugin with the Spring preset instead of manually adding open to every proxied class. This makes annotated classes and their members open automatically." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reduces boilerplate and risk of forgetting open on a proxied class, which would cause runtime failures." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_5cacd608 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Spring Data repository interfaces" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Replace Java Optional<T> return types with Kotlin nullable T? in Spring Data repository interfaces for idiomatic usage." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin has built-in null safety; nullable types integrate with Kotlin's type system whereas Optional adds unnecessary wrapping." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_744609cc a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting any Spring component with dependency injection" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use @Autowired on constructors in Kotlin. Remove the annotation and the import — Spring auto-discovers the single primary constructor." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin's primary constructor syntax makes @Autowired redundant and its presence is non-idiomatic." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b57822b1 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Spring Boot main application classes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "SpringApplication.run() requires the spread operator *args for the varargs parameter, and class literals use App::class.java. Prefer runApplication<T>(*args) top-level extension." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin does not auto-spread Java varargs; omitting * causes a compilation error." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_bb0d9ae4 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Spring classes that use proxy-based features (transactions, configuration bindings, CGLIB proxies)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Classes annotated with @Transactional or @ConfigurationProperties must be declared open. @Bean methods in @Configuration classes must also be open." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Spring creates CGLIB proxies via subclassing; final classes prevent proxy creation and cause runtime errors." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_bf6ad0a6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting @Value annotations with property placeholders" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Escape $ in @Value SpEL expressions as \\$ to prevent Kotlin string template interpolation. Example: @Value(\"\\${app.name}\") val appName: String" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin interprets ${} as string templates; escaping prevents compile-time errors and incorrect string resolution." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e6e90767 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting @ConfigurationProperties classes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Convert @ConfigurationProperties to a data class only if properties are immutable. For mutable configuration that Spring populates post-construction, use a regular open class with lateinit var." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Spring requires setter methods for binding; data classes are immutable by default and cannot be populated by Spring's property binding mechanism." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e89b4a5a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Spring MVC controller annotations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Replace Java array initializer syntax in annotation parameters with Kotlin arrayOf(). Preserve @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PostMapping, and other Spring MVC annotations exactly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin does not support Java's curly-brace array initializer syntax; arrayOf() is the idiomatic replacement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

